<% if is_admin? %>
  <h1>Help page</h1>

  <div class="help-div">
    <h2>Navigation Bar</h2>
    <p><b>Manage Teams</b> - Allows you to create and delete teams</p>
    <p><b>Manage Users</b> - Allows you to create and delete users</p>
    <p><b>Feedback & Ratings</b> - Takes you to the Feedback & Rating page. Shows 
                                        Feedback on Team and associated ratings.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="help-div">
    <h2>Admin Code</h2>
    <p>The admin code is used to allow other professors to sign up with admin rights. To use, send the
    code to an admin, and instruct them to enter the code into the 'Team/admin code' field upon signup.</p>
    <p>In case the code is leaked, select 'Regenerate Code' to reset & regenerate the admin code. When this is done,
    the previous code will be invalidated.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="help-div">
    <h2>Team Summary View </h2>
    <p><b>Urgency/Intervention Level</b> - This displays the overall urgency of the Teams's feedback.<br>
                                           The Team's urgency was calcuated based on their participation, effort, and punctuality ratings.<br>
                                           Values can be either <i>"No feedback", "High","Medium", or "Low" </i> and the status colour reflects the urgency as blue, red, yellow, or green respectively.<br>
                                           <br>
                                           Scenarios that can result in a <i>"High"</i> and status of red:
                                           <ul>
                                           <li>If more than half of the team does not submit feedback for the week </li>
                                           <li>If at least one member of the team has an individual priority of "High"</li>
                                           <li>If any of the average participation, effort, or punctuality ratings are on the lower end of the scale (between 1 and 2.333)</li>
                                           </ul>
                                           <br>
                                           Scenarios that can result in a <i>"Medium"</i> and status of yellow:
                                           <ul>
                                           <li>If less than half the team did not submit feedback, but at least one member still has not submitted</li>
                                           <li>If any of the average participation, effort, or punctuality ratings are in the middle of the scale (between 2.333 and 3.666)</li>
                                           </ul>
                                           <br>
                                           Scenarios that can result in a <i>"Low"</i> and status of green:
                                           <ul>
                                           <li>If all team members have submitted their feedback and their average participation, effort, or punctuality ratings are in the higher end of the scale (between 3.666 and 5)</li>
                                           </ul>
                                           <br>
                                           Scenarios that can result in <i>"No feedback"</i> and status of blue:
                                           <ul>
                                           <li>If there are no team members on the team</li>
                                           </ul> 
    </p>
    <p><b>Average Rating (Out of 5)</b> - Average rating from team members feedback.</p>
    <p><b>Team Name</b> - The assigned name to the team.</p>
    <p><b>Team Code</b> - Provide this code to students prior to signup, and instruct them to enter the code into the 
      'Team/admin code' field upon signup so they are added to the appropriate team.</p>
    <p><b>Team Members</b> - List of team members.</p>
    <p><b>View Team Aggregated Feedback</b> - Show aggregated team feedback.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="help-div">
    <h2> Feedback & Ratings Filter </h2>
    <p>There are 8 filter options:
      <ul>
        <li><b>First Name</b> - Filters for all first names that begin with your search input</li>
          <ul>
            <li>Type in the first name of the student</li>
            <li>Case-insensitive</li>
            <li>For example, if you searched "Ben", it will return any name beginning with "Ben" such as "Ben", "Benjamin" and "Benji"</li>
          </ul>
        <li><b>Last Name</b> - Filters for all last names that begin with your search input</li>
          <ul>
            <li>Works in the same way as 'First name'</li>
          </ul>
        <li><b>Team Name</b> - Filters for selected team</li>
          <ul>
            <li>Select a team name from the dropdown</li>
            <li>All team names are within the dropdown selection</li>
          </ul>
        <li><b>Participation Rating</b> - Filters for selected range of participation ratings</li>
          <ul>
            <li>For example, if 2 and 4 are selected in the 'start' and 'end' dropdowns respectively, any feedback with a participation rating of 2, 3 or 4 will be shown.</li>
          </ul>
        <li><b>Effort Rating</b> - Filters for selected range of effort ratings</li>
        <li><b>Punctuality Rating</b> - Filters for selected range of punctuality ratings</li>
        <li><b>Priority</b> - Filters for selected priority</li>
        <li><b>Timestamp</b> - Filters for all timestamps within the selected time range</li>
          <ul>
            <li>Start and end dates are included in the range</li>
            <li>By default, the end date is today's date</li>
          </ul>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <p>
      Click the filter button to apply the filters.
    </p>
    <p>
      After filters are applied, they will show underneath. Click the reset button to clear the applied filters.
    </p>
    <p>
      You may select from any number of filter options. If any options are left blank, they are ignored.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p><%= link_to 'Back', :back %></p>
<% end %>